Doing so was not illegal but the expenditure was illegal under s. 17 of the 1883 Act. || 4 O'M & H 70; HCP 1886 177 p. 39-53

The 1883 by-election for Ipswich was held when the sitting Conservative MP Thomas Clement Cobbold died.  It was won by the Liberal candidate Henry Wyndham West.  The unsuccessful conservative candidate was William Thomas Charley.
